metadata.name: Curiosity
metadata.description:
Rays of winter sunlight shining down on this little black-backed jackal. Curiosity at its finest, offering me the greatest photo opportunity I have ever had of these stunning wanderers. The fox-like animals, often mistaken for small wolfs, are a special sight to behold. They scavenge for food, even stealing the meals of large predators such as lions. Which is what makes this unique 1 of 1 edition of these cute, yet daredevil mammals, a wonderful addition to any wildlife photography collection. This piece is for collectors seeking to accumulate the highest quality, unique, and stunning items found on the market.

Location: The Kruger National Park, South Africa
